  "text": "XPCOM Component Implementation Pattern Analysis\n\nThis analysis reveals the established patterns for implementing Firefox XPCOM components. The key components are:\n\n1. HEADER FILE PATTERN (nsObserverService.h, ClearSiteData.h):\n   - Define a class inheriting from interfaces (e.g., nsIObserver)\n   - Use NS_DECL_ISUPPORTS macro to declare QueryInterface, AddRef, Release methods\n   - Use NS_DECL_NSIOBSERVER (or equivalent) to declare interface methods\n   - Use private destructor and default constructor\n   - Define component CID using NS_OBSERVERSERVICE_CID pattern\n\n2. IMPLEMENTATION FILE PATTERN (nsObserverService.cpp, ClearSiteData.cpp):\n   - Use NS_IMPL_ISUPPORTS(ClassName, InterfaceList) macro to implement reference counting and QueryInterface\n   - This macro expands to call NS_IMPL_ADDREF, NS_IMPL_RELEASE, and NS_IMPL_QUERY_INTERFACE\n   - Implement interface methods using NS_IMETHODIMP macro\n   - NS_IMPL_ADDREF and NS_IMPL_RELEASE manage the mRefCnt member variable\n   - Reference counting uses increment/decrement with stabilization when refcount reaches zero\n\n3. FACTORY PATTERN (ModuleUtils.h):\n   - NS_GENERIC_FACTORY_CONSTRUCTOR(_InstanceClass) creates a factory function\n   - This macro generates: static nsresult ClassName##Constructor(REFNSIID aIID, void** aResult)\n   - Factory creates new instance with RefPtr, then calls QueryInterface\n   - Component is registered with contract IDs like \"@mozilla.org/component-name;1\"\n\n4. REFERENCE COUNTING (nsISupportsImpl.h):\n   - NS_DECL_ISUPPORTS declares: QueryInterface, AddRef (returns nsrefcnt), Release (returns nsrefcnt)\n   - AddRef increments mRefCnt and returns new count\n   - Release decrements mRefCnt and deletes object when count reaches zero\n   - Stabilization prevents re-entrance during destruction\n   - QueryInterface uses interface tables for runtime type checking\n\n5. TOOLKIT COMPONENTS EXAMPLE (toolkit/components/):\n   - ClearSiteData.h/cpp demonstrates a real component implementing nsIObserver\n   - Located in toolkit/components/clearsitedata/\n   - Shows integration with XPCOM component system\n   - Uses the same macros for cross-platform compatibility\n\n6. DOCUMENTATION (writing-xpcom-interface.rst):\n   - Components require .idl file for interface definition\n   - XPIDL_SOURCES added to moz.build for auto-generation\n   - components.conf file registers component with CID, contract ID, and C++ type\n   - Services.js integration for JavaScript access\n   - Uses mozilla namespace for implementation classes\n\nThe MyComponent.h and MyComponent.cpp files implement this pattern with an nsIObserver implementation, and MyComponent.cpp.factory shows the registration pattern using NS_GENERIC_FACTORY_CONSTRUCTOR macro."
}

